subjective.chief_complaint: Generally unwell, sore throat, runny nose
subjective.hpi: 4-day history of generally feeling unwell, sore throat, runny nose, fatigue, myalgia, and joint pain. Sore throat is improving. Reports dry constant cough and nasal congestion. Night sweats present for 4 days. Fever initially reported but settling with paracetamol/ibuprofen. Reports shortness of breath on exertion. Headaches are generalized and intermittent without visual symptoms or photophobia. No nausea, vomiting, chest pain, bowel/urinary symptoms, or rashes. Appetite reduced but drinking fluids.
subjective.patient_history: Past Medical History: nil. Drug History: nil. NKDA (No Known Drug Allergies). Family History: Grandmother with Type 2 Diabetes Mellitus. Social History: Lives alone, accountant, occasional smoker and alcohol drinker. Work is stressful with no mood symptoms.

primary_diagnosis.value: Viral Upper Respiratory Tract Infection (URTI) / Influenza

plan.patient_instructions: Conservative management: Rest, push fluids, regular paracetamol/ibuprofen. Monitor temperature. Discussed red flag symptoms (shortness of breath, chest pain, fevers); if present, urgent review with Doctor is required.
